episodes.overview: A couple is ready to take their relationship to the next level and search for a home on Long Island, New York. He's looking to buy an old fixer, but she wants to spend their max on something turnkey that's near her mom.

episodes.name: Equity in the DMV
episodes.overview: A young couple is finally in the position to buy after moving back in with relatives to save for a house in Washington, DC. She grew up in old homes and prefers something modern, but he's in finance and wants the most bang for their buck with a fixer.

episodes.name: Portland Architect's Housing Plan
episodes.overview: An architect wants a piece of property where she can create multiple units in Portland, Oregon. Her boyfriend is also on board with the plan, as long as there's no massive renovation involved.

episodes.name: Shaking Things Up in Colorado
episodes.overview: After twenty years of marriage, New Jersey natives look to shake things up and start a new life in Colorado Springs. She has her heart set on a historic charmer in town, but he's dreaming of a modern mountain paradise farther out.

episodes.name: Litigating a Living Room
episodes.overview: Married lawyers look to buy their first home in the Tampa Bay area. She wants a brand-new, modern home with a large kitchen, but he's all about negotiating for a bargain house with a dedicated room for his sports memorabilia.

episodes.name: Island Life in Charleston
episodes.overview: A couple looks to upgrade to a coastal cottage in Charleston, South Carolina. She's worried about overspending while he's willing to go to their max, but in this very popular market, they each may have to compromise.

episodes.name: From Boston to New Hampshire
episodes.overview: Boston newlyweds are packing up to start a family in New Hampshire. He wants to be secluded with a modern cabin in the woods, but she's looking for a house with lots of charm that's around neighbors.

episodes.name: Starting a Family Legacy in Chicago
episodes.overview: A brother and sister are pooling their resources to buy a home together in Chicago. He wants a modern, single-family home they can all live in together, but she wants a charming multi-family property with completely separate units for each of them.

episodes.name: Lovebirds or Landlords in Chicago
episodes.overview: A couple who met only six months ago has decided to take the plunge into homeownership in Chicago. One wants to invest in a vintage multi-unit property with income potential, but the other wants a modern full-amenity building just for the two of them.

episodes.name: Leaning Toward Luxury in Dallas
episodes.overview: A single mom is on the hunt for her first home in Dallas. Her new boyfriend is helping in the search, and he wants her to consider a lower priced fixer, but she's leaning toward spending top dollar to get something that's move-in ready.

episodes.name: Creative Eye in Seattle
episodes.overview: After moving all over the country, a buyer looks to put down roots near friends and family in Seattle. She has the eye of a creative director, which doesn't always jive with her budget, so her best friend is along to help keep things in perspective.

episodes.name: Bright Future in Missouri
episodes.overview: After getting through a serious health scare, a couple looks to buy a large family home in Missouri. She's an agent who wants a great deal on a newer home, but he's a builder who would love to get his hands on an old Victorian.

episodes.name: A Home in the Hills of West Virginia
episodes.overview: A husband and wife search for a bigger house for their growing family in the hills of Charleston, West Virginia. They're looking for plenty of outdoor space for their kids to play, but in their area, finding flat and usable land can be a challenge.

episodes.name: A Family Move to Orlando
episodes.overview: Newlyweds from Colorado head south to be near family in Orlando, Florida. He wants a home that's new, modern and smart, but she's in love with all things vintage and doesn't mind spending big.

episodes.name: Getting Their Fish On in Nashville
episodes.overview: A country music artist and his manager wife look to buy their first home together in Nashville. She wants to play it safe and get something that's under their means, but he won't settle for anything less than his big dream house on the water for fishing.

episodes.name: Struggling to Compromise in Raleigh
episodes.overview: In need of more space, a couple looks to buy their first home in Raleigh, North Carolina. Up against a tough market, he's willing to take on projects or consider townhomes, but she's determined to find a single-family home that's move-in ready.

episodes.name: Dream Home Near Lake Michigan
episodes.overview: Buyers can finally afford to purchase property after moving from New York City to the Grand Rapids area near Lake Michigan. One wants to play it safe with a smaller and less-expensive home, but the other wants to spend big for a large house by the lake.

episodes.name: A Life-Changing Move in Texas
episodes.overview: Newlyweds look to move from Austin to their hometown of Belton, Texas. Her style is contemporary cottage while he's looking for something more traditional, but it's up to her mom to guide these first-time buyers into a house they can agree on.

episodes.name: Missing Her Family in Mississippi
episodes.overview: A woman is returning home to be near her aging parents and grandchildren in Mississippi. She won't budge on finding the perfect two-story Craftsman, and her two best friends are having trouble getting her to compromise.

episodes.name: An Oasis in the California Desert
episodes.overview: A young couple about to become first-time parents moves from Las Vegas to be closer to family in Southern California. She wants a stress-free, turnkey home, but he's a former Air Force mechanic and isn't afraid to get his hands dirty to save some money.

episodes.name: To Finally Say That We're Home
episodes.overview: A couple that dated long distance is now engaged and looking for a home together in Louisiana. She's looking for a newer place in a family friendly area, but he wants something with privacy and land.

episodes.name: Racing Around in Indy
episodes.overview: An Indiana native is committed to buying a charming place similar to his childhood home in Indianapolis. He wants a place that's downtown and big enough for a future family, but he'll have to decide between living for now or living for the future.

episodes.name: Craftsman vs. Midcentury in St. Paul
episodes.overview: Newlywed engineers have outgrown their small apartment and need more space before starting a family in St. Paul. He's willing to spend for a charming Craftsman, but she's set on a classic midcentury modern with project potential at a bargain price.

episodes.name: New Baby and New Home in Chicago
episodes.overview: A couple with a baby on the way looks to get out of their basement apartment and into a home of their own in Chicago. She wants a place that's contemporary with an elevator, but he's a huge fan of vintage architecture.

episodes.name: There Can Only Be One
episodes.overview: Two twenty-something engineers in a new relationship are moving in together in Minneapolis. If they decide to go with her city bungalow, she'll take on the mortgage, but if they find his home in the suburbs, he'll sign his name on the dotted line.

episodes.name: What an Old House Means in New Orleans
episodes.overview: A newlywed couple with a baby on the way is having difficulty finding their first home in New Orleans. He wants a historic shotgun-style place right in the action of the city, but she's looking for a quiet home to raise their family in the suburbs.

episodes.name: Seizing the Day in New England
episodes.overview: Newlyweds are put to the test as they search for a classic New England charmer. He wants to spend top dollar for a big house where he can add sweat equity, but she's a penny pincher and doesn't want to overextend themselves.

episodes.name: Downsizing For a Dream House
episodes.overview: A couple wants out of their high maintenance home for something smaller and easier to care for near Minneapolis. She wants a place that's unique, even if it comes at a price, but he wants to spend as little as possible to save for a future dream house.

episodes.name: Battling Besties in Atlanta
episodes.overview: Two twenty-something best friends have decided they each want to buy their own first home in Atlanta. They're looking for separate houses together, but with identical price ranges and similar wants, the hunt could bring them closer or create competition.

episodes.name: South Carolina Winemakers
episodes.overview: Young newlyweds are ready to search for a home to purchase in South Carolina. They're looking for something close to their jobs, and they also want a place that can accommodate their ambitious winemaking side business.

episodes.name: Residency in Minnesota
episodes.overview: Resident doctors are moving to her hometown of Rochester, Minnesota, to buy their first home and start a family. He's looking for a country fixer with some land, but she thinks a modern, turnkey place that's close to town would be better suited for them.

episodes.name: Last Move to Downtown Cincinnati
episodes.overview: A military family is making their tenth relocation, this time to downtown Cincinnati. They're hoping this will be their last move, so she's hoping for a charming historic home with room to grow, but he's favoring a place that's turnkey contemporary.

episodes.name: Getting Quirky in West Virginia
episodes.overview: A single mom looks to buy her first home so her young son can be closer to family in Charleston, West Virginia. She's focused on finding an older home that's as quirky as she is, but her mom thinks she should find something that's lower maintenance.

episodes.name: Suddenly Single in the South
episodes.overview: A newly single woman is excited to start a new chapter of her life with a home in Charleston, South Carolina. Her young daughter thinks she should downsize, but she's stuck on getting the large single-family house with a pool that she had previously.

episodes.name: More to Love and More to Shovel in Minnesota
episodes.overview: Two young professionals search for a place after landing dream jobs in Minnesota. One of them is from the area and wants a historic house to fix up like he's always dreamed of, but the other is all about a sleek modern home they can move into right away.

episodes.name: Getting It All in the Kansas Suburbs
episodes.overview: A couple didn't get everything they wanted in their last home, so this time they're hoping to get it all in the Kansas suburbs. She's looking for a midcentury modern house, but he has his eyes set on a new build.

episodes.name: A Bigger House Before the Baby Near Boston
episodes.overview: North Shore Boston newlyweds are expecting their first child and need a bigger place. They're looking to get out of their one bedroom apartment, but they have very different ideas of what their family dream home should look like, and what it should cost.

episodes.name: Suburbs vs. City in Minneapolis
episodes.overview: A duo looks to move from a small town to the big city of Minneapolis. One wants a more quiet life in the suburbs, but the other prefers a more urban feel.

episodes.name: Town or Country in Alaska
episodes.overview: A couple searches for a home with more space so they can grow their young family in Anchorage, Alaska. He wants something with the cabin feel he grew up with and lots of land, but she's from the lower 48 and wants something updated and closer to town.

episodes.name: A Family Home in South Georgia
episodes.overview: After relocating from Montana less than a year ago, a couple is ready to move their family out of a rental and buy their own home in South Georgia. He grew up in the South and loves Southern charm, but she wants something that's more contemporary.

episodes.name: Whimsy Wanted in New York
episodes.overview: Buyers outside of New York City sold their apartment in less than a week, so now they need to find a new home fast. He wants to go with something small to keep costs down, but she's got her heart set on a large house with charm and a whimsical feel.

episodes.name: Leaving Winter Behind in Florida
episodes.overview: A couple decides to leave New Jersey and relocate with their four kids to sunny Boca Raton, Florida. She wants a home with a Mediterranean vibe, but he's after something that's more modern.

episodes.name: Arizona Astronaut Seeks Space
episodes.overview: A female astronaut turned artist seeks a midcentury modern home where she can make her creative dreams a reality in Mesa, Arizona. Her more practical best is worried, however, that she'll take on a major fixer-upper and overspend.

episodes.name: Body Slams and Big Houses in Orlando
episodes.overview: A former professional wrestler is looking for a showcase home in Orlando, Florida. He wants a fun place for throwing big parties, but his spiritual practitioner wife prefers a more tranquil home to start a family.

episodes.name: Sweet Home Cincinnati
episodes.overview: A couple looks to relocate to her hometown of Cincinnati. She has her heart set on the trendy neighborhoods she dreamed of living in when she was a kid, but he's not impressed by zip codes and wants to prioritize space for their future family.

episodes.name: Trying to Downsize in Grand Rapids
episodes.overview: A Michigander is hoping to downsize from her previous home that had a headache's heap of upkeep. She's zeroed in on Grand Rapids for its exciting city life, but she's also tempted to head out to the suburbs for the familiar lure of space.

episodes.name: Log Cabin Dreams in Washington
episodes.overview: High school sweethearts look to relocate from Ohio for his new job in Burlington, Washington. He hopes to fulfill his lifelong dream of buying a log cabin, but she wants a vintage farmhouse that she can make her own.

episodes.name: Young Buyer Wants a Project in Vermont
episodes.overview: A twenty-something amateur wood worker wants to take on a project for her first home in Burlington, Vermont. Her BFF is worried she'll get in over her head and hopes to steer her toward something more updated.

episodes.name: Hoosier DJ's Sample Homes
episodes.overview: A couple is bursting at the seams in their tiny apartment with three growing boys in Portage, Indiana. She wants a home that reminds her of the '90s sitcoms she grew up watching, but he prefers something so big he can get lost in his own basement retreat.

episodes.name: Military Family Heads to Nashville
episodes.overview: After many years in the Coast Guard, a fun-loving couple decides to move their family to Nashville. With their experience in military housing, she's ready for something they can put their own stamp on, and he wants a lower-priced home that's turnkey.

episodes.name: Needs Convincing in Washington
episodes.overview: A couple can't agree on whether to stay where they are or upgrade to another home in Washington. He wants to convince her to spend more on a place with land that's large and modern, but she's worried about cost and would prefer a cozy cottage.

episodes.name: Ready for Adventure in Alaska
episodes.overview: A couple decides to go for an unexpected job opportunity and move to Fairbanks, Alaska. He's looking for a rustic A-frame, but she wants something traditional that feels like home.

episodes.name: Twin Cities House Hack
episodes.overview: New parents are looking to get out of his apartment and into their first home in the Twin Cities. She wants a cozy farmhouse with a garden, but he's feeling the pressure of buying on just one income and prefers a place they can both live in and rent.

episodes.name: Arizona Couple's City Dilemma
episodes.overview: A blended family with a baby on the way searches for a new home, but can't agree on where to live. One wants Arizona's up-and-coming and affordable community of Peoria, but the other prefers the established and expensive city of Scottsdale.

episodes.name: Independent Again in California
episodes.overview: After living with her parents for the past two years, a single buyer is ready to buy her own place in Los Angeles. She's looking for an updated single-family house in the city, but her mom thinks a low maintenance condo in the suburbs is the way to go.

episodes.name: Goodbye Army, Hello Long Island
episodes.overview: After years of living in military housing, a retiring Army instructor and his wife are buying their first home on Long Island. She's an interior designer and has been dreaming of getting into a two-story with character, but he wants a ranch with a pool.

episodes.name: Searching for Forever in Savanna
episodes.overview: Married first-time buyers are looking for a house they can grow into with their young family in Savannah, Georgia. He's determined to get a complete fixer, but she works in real estate and thinks that a more practical, move-in ready home would be best.

episodes.name: All the Family in Virginia
episodes.overview: With a baby on the way, a couple's ready to level up from their townhouse to a bigger home that can also accommodate extended family in Northern Virginia. He wants something grand that shows their success, but she prefers a place that's more contemporary.

episodes.name: Living the Los Angeles Dream
episodes.overview: A family needs a home with a lot more space for themselves and their young son, but that comes at a pretty penny in pricey Los Angeles. One is an interior designer and wants an affordable fixer with vintage charm, but the other prefers something modern.

episodes.name: Character vs. Modern in Arizona
episodes.overview: A couple looks to purchase their first home together in Arizona. One is pushing for an older place and she's determined to stick to her price range, but the other is fine with spending more to get something modern.

episodes.name: Off to College in Lubbock
episodes.overview: Benevolent parents look to purchase a home for their sons to live in while they attend college in Lubbock, Texas. They want an older ranch with projects to increase resale value, but the boys would rather find something new that requires no work.

episodes.name: Hunting for a House and a Man in Charlotte
episodes.overview: A single New Jersey woman moves for work and to hopefully find the Southern man of her dreams in Charlotte, North Carolina. She's an interior designer who has her heart set on a fixer-upper, but her friend thinks she should find something more manageable.

episodes.name: A Home Grandma Would Love
episodes.overview: An up-and-coming fashion model is on the hunt for a house that she can turn into an extended family hub in Atlanta. She's all about charm and projects, but her cousin thinks she should buy something less nostalgic that doesn't require any work.

episodes.name: Show Me a Place in Missouri
episodes.overview: A Canadian couple moves stateside for university jobs and looks for a home in Springfield, Missouri. She wants a rustic, prairie home like she grew up in, but he's pushing for an open concept, single-level home to accommodate his brother when he visits.

episodes.name: Stunt Actors Need a Home Fast
episodes.overview: Stunt performers look to buy a home in Atlanta before their upcoming wedding. He wants a brick Colonial with space for a media room to prepare for his jobs, but she's focused on a modern farmhouse with a soaking tub to help her recuperate from work.

episodes.name: An Upgrade in Connecticut
episodes.overview: A couple is at odds over how much house to buy in Connecticut. He's a doctor who wants to go big, but she's trying to convince him that a more modest home would be better.

episodes.name: Room for Mom in Atlanta
episodes.overview: A hard-working mother searches for a home big enough for herself and her two sons in Atlanta. She's torn between a fixer or a new build, and her mother also wants to move in, so finding a house with an extra en suite may prove to be a challenge.

episodes.name: Where's the Beach in Pennsylvania?
episodes.overview: A couple looks to relocate from sunny California to the Pennsylvania-New Jersey area. She wants a larger home to raise their daughter near her family, but he's hoping to find a beach house on the Jersey Shore.

episodes.name: Knock Down Walls vs. Cannonballs
episodes.overview: A family looks to relocate for more space and to be close to the beach in Bradenton, Florida. She's ready to renovate to get exactly what they need, but he wants something that's move-in ready with a pool for their young boys.

episodes.name: Twin Team Up in Twin Cities
episodes.overview: Twin brothers look for a first home purchase for the younger of the two in St. Paul, Minnesota. The older brother is focused on his sibling's finances, but the younger won't settle for anything less than what he has for his vision.

episodes.name: More for Less in Chicago Suburbs
episodes.overview: Priced out of San Francisco, a family relocates to buy a place near family with more space for their boys in the Chicago suburbs. She's ready to spend what it takes to get a rancher on a huge lot, but he's looking for a modern home at a bargain price.

episodes.name: Island Life vs. Space in Florida
episodes.overview: A couple looks to be close to friends and family and move from Mississippi to his hometown of St. Augustine, Florida. He's willing to pay top dollar for a beach house by the water, but she wants to go inland so they can get more house for their money.

episodes.name: Back Home Again in Iowa
episodes.overview: After losing a mom to cancer, a duo looks to start over close to family and friends in Des Moines, Iowa. One loves the idea of an updated rancher, but the other is willing to put in some sweat equity on a historical two-story with character.

episodes.name: Unsure On the Jersey Shore
episodes.overview: A young couple is ready to purchase their first home in New Jersey. She's looking for a waterfront property, but he would rather invest in a fixer-upper.

episodes.name: City or Country in St. Louis
episodes.overview: An artist and entrepreneur is ready to make his first home purchase in the St. Louis area. He's torn between a vintage home in historic downtown or more space and quiet in the country, so he's looking to his high school friend for help with the decision.

episodes.name: Victorian Vibes
episodes.overview: An expectant mother needs to find a new home fast in Atlanta. She wants a cozy Victorian with a wood-burning fireplace, but with her aunt and protective father along on the hunt, she'll have to maintain her vision against strong family opinions.

episodes.name: Bigger or Better in South Carolina
episodes.overview: A family of six needs out of their rental and into a larger home of their own in Lexington, South Carolina. She's ready to spend it all to stay in their golf cart community, but he wants to go farther out for less money.

episodes.name: Finally Settling Down in Ohio
episodes.overview: With his military career coming to an end, a couple is ready to find a long-term home to raise their four daughters in Ohio. He's confident in his ability to fix anything, but after nine moves in 18 years, she wants something easy and move-in ready.

episodes.name: House Then Wedding in Florida
episodes.overview: After getting engaged, a young couple is ready to find their first house together in Fort Lauderdale, Florida. She's from Ukraine, and he's from Jamaica, so they're bringing in a friend to help navigate their differing ideas about what feels like home.

episodes.name: New City, New Baby in Charlotte
episodes.overview: Newlyweds who recently relocated from Ohio are in a hurry to find a home before their first child arrives in Charlotte, North Carolina. She's eager to find a Southern-style home with a huge yard, but he wants a sleek and modern place in walkable Uptown.

episodes.name: Hunting for a Homestead
episodes.overview: A married couple that's lived a long-distance relationship is finally coming together to buy their first home in Grand Rapids. He wants acreage to start a homestead away from the city, but she prefers to start small with a little plot of land in town.

episodes.name: Long-Awaited Boston Dreamhouse
episodes.overview: A sixth-grade science teacher is finally ready to buy her dream house in the Boston area. She wants a single-family home with an updated kitchen, but her youngest son will be living with her, and he's trying to score some space to record his podcast.

episodes.name: Moving Home to Ohio
episodes.overview: Wanting to be closer to family, a couple looks to move from California to Columbus, Ohio. They're hoping that their money will stretch a lot farther, and she loves the idea of a lower-priced historic fixer, but he's desperate for something brand new.

episodes.name: Baby Makes Six in Delaware
episodes.overview: A couple needs to find a bigger home before baby number four arrives in Delaware. She wants vintage charm and a place for a home salon, but he's looking for something that's modern and move-in ready.

episodes.name: Downsizing in Alabama
episodes.overview: With their kids grown, a married couple is relocating for his job to Huntsville, Alabama. She's pushing for a spacious house in the suburbs where they can make new friends, but he thinks a smaller home in a walkable area is better for their stage in life.

episodes.name: A Better Life in Florida
episodes.overview: A young woman and her husband have worked hard to save up and buy their first house in Florida. After growing up in a trailer, he's ready to spend for a spacious two-story home, but she's pushing for a single-story that's lower priced and modern.

episodes.name: Cozy Home in Upstate New York
episodes.overview: A recent divorcee looks to buy a home for her son, her boyfriend and his kids when they come to visit in upstate New York. She's working with limited funds, so her search to find the perfect home big enough to accommodate everyone will be a challenge.

episodes.name: Space to Meditate in Houston
episodes.overview: After years of buying with other people in mind, a woman is finally looking for a home just for herself in Houston. As a life coach, she wants an office and a meditation room for clients, but her daughter thinks she should get something low maintenance.

episodes.name: Engaged in Atlanta
episodes.overview: A recently engaged couple looks to buy a home in the Atlanta area before they focus on planning their wedding. He wants a fixer-upper to save money on the mortgage, but she insists on a place that's fully updated, and she's willing to pay more to get it.

episodes.name: Rugby Players in Richmond
episodes.overview: Rugby players are ready to commit to purchasing a home together in Richmond, Virginia. He's an experienced buyer and is ready to go big with their budget, but even though she's aggressive on the field, she's got first-time buyer's cold feet.

episodes.name: Foundation for a Family in Ohio
episodes.overview: A young couple's ready to buy their first home together in Columbus, Ohio. He's nervous about overspending and prefers a smaller place that needs work, but she wants a big, turnkey house with plenty of space for future kids.

episodes.name: How I Feel About Vinyl Siding
episodes.overview: A couple looks to move back to his hometown of Hanover, Pennsylvania. She's always dreamed of living in a historic home that's packed with character, but he's an engineer who doesn't want to deal with hundred-year-old problems.

episodes.name: Picky in O.C.
episodes.overview: Lifelong renters are finally ready to buy their first home in Orange County, California. One demands turnkey perfection, but the other is sweating the high prices of property in the Golden State, so he wants a low-priced fixer.

episodes.name: Michigan Family Lake Life
episodes.overview: A Michigan couple has been saving up to buy a lake home where they can make family memories. She wants a small and affordable ranch, but he wants a lot of space and is willing to spend to get it.

episodes.name: Best for Baby in Detroit
episodes.overview: An expectant couple looks to buy a house before their baby is born in Detroit. She wants an updated ranch that's family friendly, but he's pushing for an older Craftsman that reminds him of his own childhood.

episodes.name: Desperately Seeking Southern
episodes.overview: A young couple relocates for their careers to Athens, Georgia. She's adamant they find a home that suits their new Southern lifestyle with columns and large porches, but he grew up in a traditional house, so he's ready for something fresh and funky.

episodes.name: Six Years to Settle in Arizona
episodes.overview: A couple bumps up against their inability to compromise in their search for a larger family home in Phoenix. She's looking for something nice with a pool, but there's fierce competition in the area, and he wants to avoid the expense.

episodes.name: It Can Be Done in Atlanta
episodes.overview: After years of saving and rebuilding her credit, a single mother looks to finally buy a home in Atlanta. Her mom is along on the search, but she's concerned most with finding her daughter a house that she can fill with her antiques.

episodes.name: East vs. West Atlanta
episodes.overview: With an unexpected third child on the way, a family needs a new house fast in Atlanta. One wants to stay on the East side and splurge on a Colonial that feels homey, but the other wants to move to the West side so they can spend less.

episodes.name: High Expectations in Houston
episodes.overview: After putting everything she had into her business, an interior designer is ready to put herself first and buy a home in Houston. Waiting for years to buy means her expectations are now sky-high, but her bestie is along to try and keep her grounded.

episodes.name: State Hopping on the East Coast
episodes.overview: Buyers are in a hurry to purchase their first home together before their lease expires and the rent skyrockets in Delaware. One wants a cozy midcentury modern ranch, while the other's Type A personality requires a unique, historic home.

episodes.name: Back from Abroad in Florida
episodes.overview: After working abroad for several years in Australia, a young couple returns to buy a home in the Florida Panhandle. They need plenty of room to start a family, and he's willing to spend for high-end finishes, but she prefers something more affordable.

episodes.name: Things Are Getting Better
episodes.overview: After a divorce, a single dad looks for a fresh start with a new home for himself and his daughter in Florida. He wants something grand and near the water, but his best friend is worried that he's getting in over his head.

episodes.name: Living Her Best Life in Minneapolis
episodes.overview: Recently divorced and ready to buy on her own, a young woman searches for an old home in Minneapolis. She's looking for a place she can put her own touches on, but her friend wants to remind her to focus on dating, rather than renovations.

episodes.name: Peace and Quiet in Arkansas
episodes.overview: A couple looks to leave bustling Bentonville, Arkansas, for a quieter setting outside of town. After their last fixer-upper, she's set on something that's turnkey, but he's willing to take on a project if he can get more land.

episodes.name: Back to the Beach in St. Augustine
episodes.overview: A surfer looks for a place near the beach in her hometown of St. Augustine, Florida. She'd like a turnkey home, but her DIY-ing mom thinks she should be open to fixer-uppers so she can have an excuse to visit her daughter on the coast.

episodes.name: Mom Knows Best in North Carolina
episodes.overview: After moving for her job a year ago, a young woman is ready to lay down roots and buy a house in North Carolina. She'd love to find something historic and charming, but her mom has flown into town to make sure her daughter makes a wise choice.

episodes.name: Practical vs. Grand in Virginia
episodes.overview: After overcoming a serious health issue, a Virginia couple needs a new home that better accommodates her needs. He's pushing for a practical and affordable single-story, but she still insists on the grand and glamorous home of her dreams no matter what.

episodes.name: From NYC to OK
episodes.overview: As part of a remote workers program, a buyer moves from a bustling New York City to Tulsa, Oklahoma. She's looking for a cozy bungalow that won't break the bank, but her big sister wants to make sure she spends enough to get a home she can enjoy.

episodes.name: Family First in Pittsburgh
episodes.overview: Newlyweds look to sell their tiny townhouse and give their growing family more space in the South Hills suburb of Pittsburgh. He wants to go farther out where they can get more for their money, but she wants something turnkey and close to the city.

episodes.name: Town or Country in Vermont

episodes.name: Searching for Space in Indiana
episodes.overview: A family wants out of his dad's house and into their own home in Northern Indiana. He wants something cool and retro, but she's set on a place that reminds her of grandma's house.

episodes.name: Seattle Space Need
episodes.overview: An avid traveler looks to settle down with her first home purchase in Seattle. With lots of hobbies and personal possessions piling up, her friend is on the hunt to help find a place that she thinks will function properly.

episodes.name: A Suburban Squabble in Chicago

episodes.name: Returning Home to Michigan
episodes.overview: A buyer returns home and looks to buy a grand house to fit his bougie taste in a trendy Michigan suburb. He's bringing his friend along for help, but she thinks what he wants and what he can afford are worlds apart.

episodes.name: From Brooklyn to the Beach
episodes.overview: A Brooklyn native looks for a home to serve as an escape from the city in Cape May, New Jersey. One of her sisters is chipping in financially, but one of the pair has a practical approach that's at odds with the other's vision to go big by the beach.

episodes.name: A Fresh Start in Philadelphia
episodes.overview: After a difficult break up, a buyer wants to start fresh with a new home in the Philadelphia area. As a first-time buyer, her wish list doesn't line up with her price range, so her best friend is along to help keep her in check.

episodes.name: Moving to Missouri
episodes.overview: After moving in with friends to save money, it's time for buyers to find their own home in Missouri. One wants a well-priced single-story home, but the other is willing to spend on an eye catching two-story to impress his friends.

Planting Roots in Baton Rouge

episodes.name: A Family Affair Near Atlanta
episodes.overview: A couple wants to trade their high maintenance horse property for a home focused around family and relaxation near Atlanta. She's French and seeks European flair, but he prefers an American traditional.

episodes.name: Cat Bistros and Charming Homes in Tampa
episodes.overview: A cat bistro owner in Tampa is dreaming of a cozy bungalow with historic charm. With a new business, she doesn't want to overspend, and with her cousin as her broker and her sister chipping in with advice, she'll have a lot to sort through.

episodes.name: Orlando High School Sweethearts

episodes.name: West Virginia Flat
episodes.overview: With their baby due soon, a couple are in a hurry to buy their first home in West Virginia. They want a flat yard for their family to play in, but given the area's rugged terrain, that may be a challenge.

episodes.name: Coffee and Colonnades in K.C.
episodes.overview: A buyer looks for a historic multi-family building to plan for his financial future in Kansas City, Missouri. He wants a larger unit to live in, and hopefully one that doesn't need as much renovation as his current place required.

episodes.name: Realist vs. Aerialist in Kansas City
episodes.overview: After moving six times in five years for his job in the Army, a couple looks to finally put down roots in Kansas City, Missouri. He wants a home that's a good investment, but she wants a house that will work for them right now.

episodes.name: Fishing for a Connecticut Lake House
episodes.overview: A buyer looks to settle down in a lake house in Connecticut. He works in construction and doesn't have time for a fixer, but he might compromise for more space.

episodes.name: New Chapter in West Hartford
episodes.overview: After a difficult break up, a single woman looks for a fresh start in West Hartford, Connecticut. She's willing to spend whatever it takes for a spacious Colonial, but her best friend is along to make sure she doesn't overextend.

episodes.name: Back From the Chicago Burbs
episodes.overview: After years of living in the suburbs, a Chicago couple wants to move back to where they met and give their kids a taste of life in the city. They have vastly different ideas of the perfect home, however, so pleasing them both may be a challenge.

episodes.name: A Pastor Plan in Florida
episodes.overview: A husband and wife pastor team searches for a home that's closer to their church in Florida. He's looking for a new build and is willing to pay for it, but she prefers a fixer-upper in order to save some money.

episodes.name: A Big Buy in Bixby
episodes.overview: A couple is ready to move on from their current home that's from his previous marriage and into a place they can call their own in Bixby, Oklahoma. He wants a place that's contemporary, but she's looking for something more traditional.

episodes.name: Space to Showcase in New Mexico
episodes.overview: A single buyer looks to move so he can be closer to family in Clovis, New Mexico. He's looking for a stylish bungalow with space for all his stuff, but he may need to get out of his comfort zone and price range in order to find the right place.

episodes.name: Newlyweds in Richmond
episodes.overview: A newlywed couple looks to move back to her hometown to start a family in Richmond, Virginia. She wants a contemporary home with a low-maintenance yard, but he's a woodworker who won't settle for less than five acres of land and a detached woodshop.

episodes.name: Twin Battle in Detroit
episodes.overview: A twenty-something looks to move back to the Detroit area where she hopes she can afford her first home. She wants a vintage single-family house in the suburbs, but her twin sister is pushing her to get a move-in ready condo that's closer to downtown.

episodes.name: Find Your Girl Gang
episodes.overview: A single professional with high-end taste looks to buy her first place in Denver. She has her girl gang of real estate specialists along for support, and she's leaning on their advice to help her stay grounded.

episodes.name: Tough Market in Maine
episodes.overview: A couple looks to get creative in their search after missing out on homes in the tough market of Portland, Maine. She wants to spend big on something vintage, but he prefers to save for a smaller home that's more conventional.

episodes.name: Learning from the Past in Birmingham
episodes.overview: A couple looks to upgrade from their starter home so they can start a family in Birmingham, Alabama. After rushing into their first place and dealing with numerous issues, they're now looking at every nook and cranny to avoid making the same mistakes.

episodes.name: For Now or Forever in Denver
episodes.overview: Newlyweds need to get out of their apartment in Denver, but have differing visions of what they should buy. She wants a single-family ranch-style house with a large yard for future kids, but he prefers a smaller, modern townhome in the heart of the city.

episodes.name: Too Big in Durham
episodes.overview: Two strong-minded engineers have landed new jobs and look to buy a vintage home in Durham, North Carolina. As an environmental engineer, she wants a smaller home that's move-in ready, but he prefers to DIY their dream home.

episodes.name: My Grand Staircase Moment
episodes.overview: Newlyweds have run out of space in their small house and need a much bigger place in Indianapolis. One is an amateur woodworker who can't wait to dive in a project, but the other can't stand the mess and wants a turnkey, grand Victorian.

episodes.name: Nail Salons and Relatives in South Carolina
episodes.overview: A young Chinese immigrant looks to buy a home big enough for her family of eight and her nail salon business in South Carolina. She's searching for a new build that has good feng shui, but finding a place that has everything she wants may be a challenge.

episodes.name: Tripping Over Toys in Illinois
episodes.overview: A couple in the Chicago suburbs needs more room for their growing family. She wants to spend less on something cozy, but he'd rather splurge on something with more space.

episodes.name: Going for Grand in Atlanta
episodes.overview: Emigrating from the Caribbean as kids, parents of twin boys have slowly climbed the real estate ladder and are now ready to buy a grand home in the Atlanta area. He loves European architecture, but she's got her heart set on something modern.

episodes.name: Chicago Burbs or Not
episodes.overview: Young parents need a bigger place for their growing family in Chicago. She wants a historic home in the city, but he wants something newer and bigger in the suburbs.

episodes.name: Building Wealth for Future Family in Chicago
episodes.overview: A couple living with his parents and saving for their first place are finally ready to buy in Chicago. She's thinking of their future kids and wants a single-family home, but he's focused on building generational wealth with a multi-unit property.

episodes.name: Making the Case for Grand in Austin
episodes.overview: A couple with very different styles looks to buy their first home together in Austin, Texas. She wants a large, grand home in the suburbs with room to grow, but he thinks a smaller midcentury modern home near the city is a better investment.

episodes.name: Escaping Wisconsin Winters to Florida
episodes.overview: After years of hard work, a married Wisconsin couple looks for a vacation home for their large family in Bradenton, Florida. She wants an affordable condo, but he prefers something that reminds him of his Spanish-style childhood home.

episodes.name: Reality vs. Reality TV
episodes.overview: An exec at HGTV and his wife look to purchase their first home in New Jersey. He wants a home that needs projects so he can put what he's learned at HGTV to work, but she'd rather pay more for something that's move-in ready.

episodes.name: Dreaming Big in Detroit
episodes.overview: After a lifetime of renting, an army veteran searches for his dream house in Detroit. He's looking for a small single-family home with a walk-in closet large enough for his extensive wardrobe, and he's also legally blind, so accessibility is key.

episodes.name: Debt-Free and Ready in KC
episodes.overview: A couple has paid off their student loans and looks to finally buy a home for their growing family in the Kansas City area. He's worried about taking on more debt and wants a small mortgage, but she thinks spending for a family home is a good investment.

episodes.name: Crazy Concepts in Kansas
episodes.overview: A traveling nurse is tired of apartments and is ready to settle down in his hometown of Overland Park, Kansas. He's enlisted his high school friend to help find his first house, but his personal tastes may be at odds with what he can afford.

episodes.name: Trading Fast Life for Family Life in Vero Beach
episodes.overview: With their first child on the way, a couple needs to trade their tiny apartment for a long-term home in Vero Beach, Florida. He prefers a lower maintenance townhome to have more time with the baby, but she wants a bigger house with a yard.

episodes.name: Downtown Denver Dreams
episodes.overview: A young professional dreams of a hip condo near all the nightlife in Denver. Her dad is putting up the down payment, so she has to stand her ground against his desire for her to find a single-family home in the suburbs.

episodes.name: Virginia is for Family
episodes.overview: A Navy man and his wife look to relocate to his hometown of Chesapeake, Virginia. He wants a low-priced fixer, but she insists on something turnkey that's large enough to accommodate family visits with an extra guest room.

episodes.name: A Place in the Poconos
episodes.overview: After a health scare, a Pennsylvania couple looks for a vacation home to make family memories in the Pocono Mountains. He aims to spend big on a move-in ready cabin, but she prefers a charming A-frame with potential.

episodes.name: Sunsets on the Sound
episodes.overview: With all of her kids grown and out of the house, a mother looks to make her favorite vacation spot her permanent home in the Outer Banks of North Carolina. She wants a prime beach location, but she may have to settle for a place smaller than she expected.

episodes.name: Searching for Historic in Kentucky
episodes.overview: A couple keeps butting heads on a home search while trying to settle their family in Fort Thomas, Kentucky. He wants a turnkey contemporary, but she's determined to find something historic, even if it means tackling projects.

episodes.name: Tight Quarters in Houston
episodes.overview: Newlyweds need to find a home for their family and tons of stuff in Houston. He's a first time buyer who wants to spend modestly on a place in the city, but this is her third purchase, and she's looking to go big in the suburbs.

episodes.name: First Home for Atlanta Dad and Grad
episodes.overview: A single dad looks to realize his dream of buying a house in his hometown of Atlanta. His daughter just graduated college and will be moving in and paying rent, and while she wants something she can put her DIY spin on, he prefers a brand-new build.

episodes.name: New Beginning in Birmingham
episodes.overview: An empty nester wants to move on from the suburbs and enjoy single life in downtown Birmingham, Alabama. He's looking for something modern at a bargain price, but his good friend is along on the search to make sure he doesn't take on too much.

episodes.name: Vintage vs. New Build in Louisville
episodes.overview: A Houston couple looks for a fresh start with a move to Louisville, Kentucky. She has her heart set on place with historical charm, but he's pushing for the convenience of new construction.
